===Noun phrase===
'''[[brain]] [[surgery]]'''
#surgery on any part of the [[nervous system]], especially the brain
#(uncountable) {{idiom}} something that is overly [[complex]], [[detail]]ed or [[confusing]]
#:''It's not '''brain surgery'''.  Just screw in the bulb and flip the switch.''

===Usage note===
*This phrase is usually used in a negative comparison, as in the example above, to show that something is (or should be) simple, straightforward, or obvious.

